    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen calling `vim.lsp.buf.references()` in neovim v0.10.4, default window looked like this, Poplist:\n\n<img width=\"1915\" height=\"415\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/93d98e5b-6e33-4d86-a280-640d453f4139\" />\n\nBut upon updating to v0.11.0, it changed to quickfix list. It may be considered as breaking, because it changes the flow of the users.\n\n<img width=\"1920\" height=\"378\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/31548879-d3e0-42a8-8d7c-8db3a11094a5\" />\n\nIdeally old behavior should be restored, but for me personally and anyone else having the same issue, it would be good if you know the way to manually revert to old behavior and have poplist.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nUpdate from nvim v0.10.4 to nvim v0.11.0\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWorkflow unchanged\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.0\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nArch Linux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nalacritty 0.15.1 (0c405d53)\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nalacritty\n\n### Installation\n\npacman",
